IRS990.ActivityOrMissionDesc: OCCHC HAS A MISSION TO TRANSITION EXTREMEMLY LOW-INCOME FAMILIES TOWARDS GREATER SELF-SUFFICIENCY BY ASSISTING THEM WITH HOUSING AND EDUCATION.
IRS990.MissionDesc: FOUNDED IN 1977, OCCHC HAS A MISSION TO TRANSITION EXTREMELY LOW-INCOME FAMILIES TOWARDS GREATER SELF-SUFFICIENCY BY ASSISTING THEM WITH HOUSING AND EDUCATION. FOR OVER 45 YEARS THE ORGANIZATION HAS CREATED AND CONTINUES TO OWN AND MANAGE 230 APARTMENTS, SERVING EXTREMELY LOW-INCOME FAMILIES IN ORANGE COUNTY. THE ORGANIZATION'S UNIQUE STANCE IN OWNING AND MANAGING ALL OF ITS UNITS ALLOWS IT TO ENHANCE THE LIVES OF ITS FAMILIES WHILE THEY LIVE IN A STABLE ENVIRONMENT CONDUCIVE TO LEARNING AND SELF-IMPROVEMENT.
IRS990.Desc: ORANGE COUNTY COMMUNITY HOUSING CORPORATION (OCCHC) PROVIDES HOUSING AND RELATED SERVICES TO LOW AND MODERATE INCOME PERSONS. DURING 2022 THE ORGANIZATION MAINTAINED UNITS AT 27 SITES. SEE SCHEDULE O ON ACCOMPLISHMENTS.

SupplementalInformationDetail.FormAndLineReferenceDesc: PROGRAM ACCOMPLISHMENTS
SupplementalInformationDetail.ExplanationTxt: Families housed by OCCHC/SteppingUP are extremely low income and struggling to make ends meet. The combination of affordable housing and free educational services through SteppingUP provides economic empowerment for the entire family and a direct path from homelessness to homeownership.In 2022, OCCHC/SteppingUP marked its 45th year in service providing safe and affordable housing to 320 families in need. It served 2,460 individuals working to step up to self-sufficiency through affordable housing and education. OCCHC/SteppingUP assisted in provided a safe, affordable home and continued to house those facing homelessness while connecting families to resources in need of rent relief, food and free program services needed to continue on a path to self-sufficiency.SteppingUP assisted in transitioning families coming from motels, shelters and substandard living to our affordable housing beginning their path to self-sufficiency. SteppingUPs Homeownership component educated 519 at-risk individuals, also providing 658 one-on-one counseling hours including budgeting, credit counseling, and financial literacy. Over 42 free bilingual workshops focused on economic security and homeownership with 5 families becoming first-time homeowners celebrating 91 homeowners to date marking our 4th year as a HUD approved agency.SteppingUPs CAP Program maintained its commitment to reducing the high school dropout rate in Orange County for 16 years; encouraging higher education for at-risk youth since 2006. The program grew from serving 26 students to serving 611 with 56 parents joining CAP's PADRE component. 32 high school seniors graduated with 100% stepping up to higher education. CAP celebrates 406 alumni with 107 CAP Alumni who have graduated college & entered the workforce.
